message.content:
cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on visual speech recognition using lip reading.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper discusses Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR) and audio-only corpus.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category as the paper deals with cross-modal distillation and frame-wise cross-entropy loss.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper discusses training models without human annotated ground truth data and leveraging unlabelled video data.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with visual and audio data for speech recognition.
